'''Menelluin''' is the [[Elvish]] name for "cornflower".

It was the emblem of [[Idril|Idril Celebrindal]], is stated to be an inlaid plaque saved from [[Gondolin]] and descending through [[Eärendil]] and his son [[Elros]] and 
influenced [[Númenóreans|Númenórean]] circular designs. The Emblem was taken to [[Gondor]] by [[Elendil]]. 

==Etymology==
The word ''menelluin'' means "sky-blue"<ref>{{HM|AI}}, p. 193</ref> in [[Quenya]] (from ''[[menel]]'' = "heavens, sky" and ''[[luine|luinë]]'' = "blue").{{fact}}

